# SPS2025 - Data Ingestion & Sequence Modeling Engine

A high-performance data processing pipeline that ingests raw time-series stock data using multiple threads, derives structured features based on stock rank transformations, and builds sequence-based models for analysis.

The system transforms raw market data into rank-based feature streams and constructs sequence-counting structures (implemented as variable-order Markov models (VOMMs), referred to here as sequence counting tries).

## Key Concepts

- Multi-threaded, high-throughput data ingestion pipeline for stock time-series data
- Rank-based feature derivation from raw market inputs
- Construction of sequence-counting trie structures
- Experimental modeling of temporal dependencies in stock movement sequences
- Multithreaded + SIMD-optimized processing (AVX-512, pthreads)
- Test-driven validation of transformation and model consistency

## Components

- **Ingestion layer** – parses raw input data efficiently
- **Transformation layer** – computes rank-based feature sequences
- **Model layer** – constructs sequence-counting trie structures (VOMMs)
- **Testing layer** – verifies correctness of transformations and model outputs

## Tech Stack

- C
- AVX-512 SIMD intrinsics
- pthreads (parallel processing)

## Notes

The project began as an exploratory system for analyzing stock data patterns and evolved into a pipeline for building sequence-based probabilistic models over derived event streams.

The “sequence counting trie” structure was independently implemented before learning it corresponds to variable-order Markov models.

## Building

This program only runs under Linux.

To get this program to build,
a file named internal_config.h will need to be created in SPS2025/C
with the following definitions:
    #define RAW_DATA_FOLDER "/your/folder"
    #define INTERMEDIATE_DATA_FOLDER "/your/folder"
    #define TREE_DATA_FOLDER "/your/folder"

RAW_DATA_FOLDER is the folder of the unzipped data from https://stooq.com/db/h/
Specifically, the daily ASCII US data.
INTERMEDIATE_DATA_FOLDER is a folder with the stooq stock files; non-nested.
TREE_DATA_FOLDER is where trees generated by the program are saved.

Once those are defined, CMake can be used to build the project.

